"title": "5207: architecture",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5207",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The design of buildings, for religious or secular use. Building designs were often regarded in Scripture as embodying spiritual truths, and capable of being divinely inspired.</p>\n<h2>Examples of architecture</h2>\n<h3>The tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:5\">HEB 8:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8-Exod25:9\">EXO 25:8–25:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:1-Exod26:37\">EXO 26:1–26:37</a></p>\n<h3>The temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:11-1Chr28:12\">1CH 28:11–28:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:1-1Kgs6:10\">1KI 6:1–6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:15-1Kgs6:38\">1KI 6:15–6:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:19\">1CH 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:1-2Chr3:17\">2CH 3:1–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:1-2Chr4:22\">2CH 4:1–4:22</a></p>\n<h3>Altars</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:31\">JOS 8:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:25\">EXO 20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:10-2Kgs16:11\">2KI 16:10–16:11</a> <em>Adopting the design of a pagan altar indicated both idolatry and submission to Assyria.</em></p>\n<h3>Ordinary dwellings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:8\">DEU 22:8</a></p>\n<h3>Ezekiel's vision of a restored temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:1-Ezek40:49\">EZK 40:1–40:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:1-Ezek41:26\">EZK 41:1–41:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:1-Ezek42:20\">EZK 42:1–42:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:10-Ezek43:17\">EZK 43:10–43:17</a></p>\n<h3>Other structures</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:4\">GEN 11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:1-1Kgs7:12\">1KI 7:1–7:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:3-Prov24:4\">PRO 24:3–24:4</a> <em>implies that a house must be more than bricks and mortar</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13-Jer22:14\">JER 22:13–22:14</a></p>\n<h2>Divinely dictated design</h2>\n<h3>The ark</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:14-Gen6:16\">GEN 6:14–6:16</a> <em>the earliest recorded example of naval architecture</em></p>\n<h2>Building design as a spiritual metaphor</h2>\n<h3>The prophecy of the rejected stone</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:22\">PSA 118:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:42\">MAT 21:42</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:10\">MRK 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:17\">LUK 20:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:7\">1PE 2:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:24-Matt7:27\">MAT 7:24–7:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:48-Luke6:49\">LUK 6:48–6:49</a> <em>the two foundations</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:10-1Cor3:13\">1CO 3:10–3:13</a> <em>the work of Christian ministers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19-Eph2:22\">EPH 2:19–2:22</a> <em>the church</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:4-1Pet2:7\">1PE 2:4–2:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:11-Isa54:12\">ISA 54:11–54:12</a> <em>the heavenly city</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:10\">HEB 11:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:9-Rev21:22\">REV 21:9–21:22</a></p>\n<h2>God as the architect of creation</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:4-Job38:5\">JOB 38:4–38:5</a></p>",
